text: The German order of precedence is a hierarchy of the government officials in the Government of Germany. It is not official, but it is used. # President of Germany # President of the Bundestag # Chancellor of Germany # President of the German Bundesrat # President of the Federal Constitutional Court ==References== Source: Order of precedence Website of the Federal Ministry of the Interior Category:Government of Germany de:Protokollarische Rangordnung#Deutschland
